I recently installed the Geospatial plugin for Girder and was excited to plot GeoJSON coordinates onto an image. I went to the REST API and went to PUT /item/{id}/geospatial under the item header. 
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/29108723/41677322-cd811aa2-747c-11e8-99d2-410909296bcb.png)

However, when I put GeoJSON coordinates that were known to work in geojson.io into the text field, I got a TypeError (string indices must be integers):
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/29108723/41677578-8ddba6f0-747d-11e8-886d-2301dac910e6.png)

The geojson.io coordinates are here:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/29108723/41677516-5e612bde-747d-11e8-9379-e9abaadb4baf.png)

And here is the code for the coordinates I used:
`{
  "type": "FeatureCollection",
  "features": [
    {
      "type": "Feature",
      "properties": {},
      "geometry": {
        "type": "Polygon",
        "coordinates": [
          [
            [
              110,
              55.32914440840507
            ],
            [
              89.20898437499999,
              55.32914440840507
            ],
            [
              89.20898437499999,
              61.897577621605016
            ],
            [
              70.048828125,
              61.897577621605016
            ],
            [
              110,
              55.32914440840507
            ]
          ]
        ]
      }
    }
  ]
}`

Is there something I wrote incorrectly above? I also changed the coordinates to integers but I still got the same "string indices must be integers" issue. I'm not sure what that refers to.

